A clear, well-worn trail cuts through the old growth here, its surface packed harder than the surrounding earth and marked by the mingled tracks of many different creatures.
The trail is flanked by @@Gdense fern-walls@@N on both sides that make it a natural corridor, and the trees overhanging it are gnarled in ways that suggest deliberate shaping rather than natural growth.
Whatever shaped these trees began shaping them long before the current generation of anything alive, and whatever the shaping was intended to produce, this trail is part of it.
