#10034
A Fern-Covered Slope~
The trail descends here down a gentle slope entirely carpeted in ferns, their fronds reaching knee-height and making the path difficult to follow except by the slight depression where generations of feet have pressed them flat.
The soil under the fern cover is loose and dark, smelling of rain and deep root-work, and the slope is studded with half-buried stones worn smooth.
At the bottom, where the natural arch of two fused trees spans the trail, the ferns grow densest of all, as though the threshold draws them toward its shade.
